Governor of Taraba State, Darius Dickson Ishaku, has approved a tax relief measure for local businesses and citizens to help curtail the effects of the noble coronavirus. According to the governor, the measures includes: extension of timeline for filing and withholding tax  return from the 21st day to the last working day of the month following the month of deduction and amongst others. This  has been described as a welcome Idea from the  governor and a step in the right direction in ensuring that SME’s in the  state suffered less from the effect of COVID-19 on the global economy. The commissioner for Finance, Dr. Jesse Ashumate, announced the measures at a press conference in Jalingo. Ashumate said the State government was conscious of the threats of COVID-19 on businesses, organisations and individuals, and approved the measures to cushion  the effects of the pandemic. According to him, “50 percent reduction on Personal Income Tax (PIT) of informal sector taxpayers made before 31st December, 2020 will attract tax relief”. “Also, use of electronic platforms for payment of taxes and processing of tax clearance certificate as well as automatic discharge of vehicles  update arrears beyond one year of expiration ending 31st December,  2020”. “Automatic waiver of 50 percent arrears volume on back duty assessment before September 2020”.